Problem Statement - Write a recursive function to check if an array is a mirror image of itself. 
This means the first half of the array should be the reverse of the second half.

class solution:
    def isMirrorImage(self, arr, n):
        # Code Here
        
       i=0
       j=n-1
       x = True
       while i<j:
           if arr[i]!=arr[j]:
               x=False
               break
           i+=1
           j-=1
       if x:
           return True
       else:
           return False
